						<p><hi rend="bold">Koṅgu, Parakēsarivarman Perumāḷ Virachōḻadeva = c. 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>In Tamil characters. Mutilated. The king is said to have reigned over the two Kongustogether. Seems to be a gift by the king to the temple of Paramēchuramuḍaiyār at Iravār in Vaigāvi-nāḍu.</p>						

